%% 3. AUTHENTICATION & AUTHORIZATION FLOW
sequenceDiagram
    participant Client
    participant Next.js
    participant Spring Boot
    participant PostgreSQL
    participant Redis

    Client->>Next.js: POST /auth/login<br/>(email, password)
    Next.js->>Spring Boot: POST /api/v1/auth/login
    Spring Boot->>PostgreSQL: SELECT user WHERE email=?<br/>(1,338ms - SLOW)
    PostgreSQL-->>Spring Boot: User record + roles
    Spring Boot->>Redis: getCachedPermissions(roles)<br/>(uses roles as cache key)
    Redis-->>Spring Boot: 500+ permissions array
    Spring Boot->>Spring Boot: Generate JWT<br/>(roles only, NO permissions)<br/>JWT size: <4096 bytes
    Spring Boot-->>Next.js: Set-Cookie: access_token<br/>(httpOnly, Secure, SameSite=Strict)
    Next.js-->>Client: 200 OK + redirect to /dashboard

    Note over Client,Redis: JWT expires in 1 hour<br/>Refresh token expires in 24 hours

    Client->>Next.js: GET /dashboard
    Next.js->>Spring Boot: GET /api/v1/dashboards/employee<br/>(Cookie: access_token)
    Spring Boot->>Spring Boot: JwtAuthenticationFilter<br/>Validate JWT signature
    Spring Boot->>Spring Boot: Extract roles from JWT
    Spring Boot->>Redis: getCachedPermissions(roles)<br/>(TTL: 1 hour)
    Redis-->>Spring Boot: Permissions array (cached)
    Spring Boot->>Spring Boot: Set SecurityContext<br/>(TenantContext + Permissions)
    Spring Boot->>Spring Boot: PermissionAspect<br/>Check @RequiresPermission("DASHBOARD:READ")
    Spring Boot->>PostgreSQL: Query dashboard data<br/>(25,146ms - CRITICAL ISSUE)
    PostgreSQL-->>Spring Boot: Dashboard data
    Spring Boot-->>Next.js: 200 OK + JSON
    Next.js-->>Client: Render dashboard

